  "time_ut": 1621524286,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0db8\u0dd8\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0dd2 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0d91\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dad \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dca\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If Samurdhi officials do not have the vaccine, they will be removed from duty",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The General Secretary of the All Ceylon Welfare and Agriculture Officers Association, Member of Parliament Mr. Jagath Kumara said that if the Samurdhi and Agriculture Development Officers are not given anti-covid vaccines in the next fortnight, they will have to leave their duties closely related to the people.",
        "The member who said that two Samurdhi officials have already been infected with Covid and died, said that in such a situation it is impossible to engage in field duties without vaccination.",
        "He also said that the government has a responsibility to provide vaccinations to other professionals working with the people.",
        "The MP said this while addressing a press conference held in Colombo yesterday.",
        "\"The government has a responsibility to reduce the number of infected people and deaths at this moment when a serious problem has arisen due to the Corona disaster. The greatest strength of the government in fulfilling that responsibility is the public servants associated with it. 5000 rupees, distribution of goods etc., as well as looking into people's needs, field officers including Samurdhi officers, village officers do a lot of work.",
        "Samurdhi officials are especially vulnerable. Currently, two Samurdhi officers have died due to Covid. About 75 others have become infected. Many more may become patients. In such a situation, the government has a responsibility to promptly provide vaccinations to all the field officers including Samurdhi officers. There is a question of how to function if this vaccine is not given. Our executive council has decided to stop working closely with the people if vaccines are not given in the next two weeks.",
        "I request the President to give enanth to Samurdhi and Agricultural Research Officers, Village Officers, Teachers, Divisional Secretaries, Bus Drivers, Conductors etc. who work closely with the people and to give priority to Samurdhi Development Officers and Samurdhi Managers. If the responsible department and ministry do not fulfill the responsibility, we have to take responsibility as a trade union.",
        "Mr. Kitsiri Gamage, President of All Ceylon Samurdhi and Agriculture Officers Association said:",
        "Samurdhi officials are facing many serious problems due to the Covid-19 situation. Last Friday, one of our brothers from Mahianganaya Kandaketiya Divisional Secretariat Division and before that a sister from Kaduwela Divisional Secretariat Division died of Covid infection. These field officers have not even been provided with health protective equipment, suits and face masks. If we don't get them, how can we go and work in the field. Therefore, instead of going to the people, we have to inform them to come to the bank and get subsidies.\" He said."
      ],
